<!--
    Sparkle appcast for Seed.

    Served at: https://procestra.app/appcast-seed.xml
    (Seed's SUFeedURL in Info.plist must point here. On launch the app
    GETs this file and compares each <sparkle:version> against the
    installed CFBundleVersion; a higher number triggers an update prompt.)

    Signing key: Seed shares the suite EdDSA key pair by design.
    SUPublicEDKey (in Seed's Info.plist) = mo0o7kL086SRjjyTW1HabtgP0ep5ECR7biu30ZmTwEQ=
    The edSignature below was produced by the matching private key, so it
    validates. (Provenance uses the same key — this is intentional.)

    Build 1 is current: installed = build 1 and this feed offers build 1,
    so no update is offered (correct). The feed only triggers an update
    when you ship a build with sparkle:version >= 2.

    To publish a new version later: bump sparkle:version (>=2) +
    shortVersionString + pubDate, upload the new DMG to R2, and update the
    enclosure url + edSignature + length (from sign_update on the new DMG),
    then deploy this file:

        .build/artifacts/sparkle/Sparkle/bin/sign_update build/Seed-<v>.dmg
        → prints sparkle:edSignature="…" length="…"
-->
